The paper deals with learning theory and algorithms for various problems, including mixtures of subcubes and decision trees with stochastic transitions. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). However, given the focus on learning algorithms and their analysis, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant because they involve related topics such as data structures, information theory, computational complexity, and artificial intelligence.
